01/12/2004
BANJA LUKA, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Republika Srpska (RS) police head Radomir Njegus resigned from his post Tuesday (30 November), following a request by RS Interior Minister Darko Matijasevic. He said police work would be more efficient without Njegus, whom he blamed for failing to round up war crimes indictees. 
In other news, RS Parliament Speaker Dusan Stojicic met with Serbian counterpart Predrag Markovic in Banja Luka on Tuesday. They jointly called on indictees to surrender, stressing the importance of fulfilling international obligations. (Dnevni avaz, Nezavisne novine, Danas - 01/12/04; Pincom.info, Fena, RTRS - 30/11/04) 
